    <refnamediv>
      <refname>&CpiaControl;</refname> <refpurpose>Control all settings of
	a CPiA based webcam via a nice GUI.</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
      <cmdsynopsis>
	<command>&CpiaControl;</command>
	<arg><replaceable>-h</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><replaceable>-d</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><replaceable>proc-file</replaceable></arg>
      </cmdsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1>
      <title>DESCRIPTION</title> <para>Control all settings of a CPiA
      based webcam via a nice GUI. This simple python-gtk application
      allows one to control a CPiA based webcam by means of a nice GUI.
      The settings are done by changing the proc-interface of the CPiA
      based webcam. Apart from a webcam you need a special
      kernel-module to use this program. See the <ulink
      URL="http://webcam.sourceforge.net">developers webpage</ulink>
      for more information. Sometimes in the future the driver will be
      part of the standard kernels.</para>
    </refsect1>
    <refsect1>
      <title>OPTIONS</title><para>
      <VARIABLELIST>
	<VARLISTENTRY>
	  <TERM><emphasis>-h</emphasis>
	  </TERM>
	  <LISTITEM>
	    <PARA> Print a help message and exit.
	    </PARA>
	  </LISTITEM>
	</VARLISTENTRY>
	<VARLISTENTRY>
	  <TERM><emphasis>-d</emphasis>
	  </TERM>
	  <LISTITEM>
	    <PARA> Additional debug output.
	    </PARA>
	  </LISTITEM>
	</VARLISTENTRY>
	<VARLISTENTRY>
	  <TERM><emphasis>proc-file</emphasis>
	  </TERM>
	  <LISTITEM>
	    <PARA>Use this file instead of the default file-name
	    <filename>/proc/cpia/video0</filename>.
	    </PARA>
	  </LISTITEM>
	</VARLISTENTRY>
      </VARIABLELIST></para>
    </refsect1>
    <refsect1>
      <title>NOTES</title><para>
      The USB cpia-driver in the development kernels 2.3.13 and
      later has no proc-interface. You need the driver from the
      web-page given above.</para>
    </refsect1>
